description.plain:
Tyler-Justin Anthony Sharpe (b. August 26, 2002), better known by his stage name, Lil Tecca, is a rapper and producer out of Queens, New York.

Tecca started rapping at age 9 because of his friends; his first song was a diss track towards his friends, which he would later take down as years went by. He would initially gain a fanbase in Toronto, Canada, leading many to mistake him for being from there, despite him coming from Queens.

He first started to gain mainstream attention with his songs “Molly Girl” and “Did It Again,” but his career would skyrocket with the release of “Ransom.” This was largely due to a Cole Bennett-directed music video, which helped the song achieve a peak at #4 on the Billboard Hot 100.

On August 30, 2019, Lil Tecca released his debut mixtape, We Love You Tecca. The project debuted and peaked at #4 on the Billboard 200 and contained five songs that reached the Billboard Hot 100, led by “Ransom.” Just a day before the release of his subsequent project, Tecca announced in a tweet that We Love You Tecca had received platinum status.

On September 18, 2020, Lil Tecca released his debut studio album, Virgo World. The album debuted and peaked at #10 on the Billboard 200 and contained two songs that reached the Billboard Hot 100, led by “Dolly” with Lil Uzi Vert.

On August 27, 2021, Lil Tecca released his second rendition of We Love You Tecca—nearly two whole years after the original. The album debuted and peaked at #10 on the Billboard 200 and contained two songs that reached the Billboard Hot 100, which was led by “NEVER LEFT” at #56, followed by the Gunna-assisted “REPEAT IT” at #80.

songs.title: Ransom

description.plain:
On “Ransom,” Lil Tecca shares some braggadocious lines about his newfound fame and the lifestyle it implies—he boasts about his luxury vehicles, designer clothes and his women.

The track was long-awaited by fans as it was previewed multiple times by the artist throughout his social medias before its initial release on May 22, 2019. The track released alongside a music video, directed by Cole Bennett of Lyrical Lemonade.

songs.title: Love Me

description.plain:
“Love Me” serves as the twelfth track on Lil Tecca’s debut mixtape We Love You Tecca. On the track, Tecca shows his affection for a woman and states the benefits of contributing to a relationship with himself.

The song was released in October 2018 but made its official re-release through Tecca’s 2019 debut mixtape We Love You Tecca and serves as one of two 2018 songs added to the mixtape alongside September 2018 track “Count Me Out.”

songs.title: Did It Again

description.plain:
Throughout “Did It Again,“ Lil Tecca raps about having sexual intercourse, making money, his exotic cars and traveling to foreign countries.

The track was originally released on January 21, 2019, becoming one of Tecca’s first hits: it eventually made it onto Tecca’s first mixtape We Love You Tecca, released on August 30, 2019.
